name: Bryce Hoppel

social_posts.post_text:
Fastest time in 2022 was 1:44 but wasn’t enough to get me where I wanted to be. The new season is a different time and we’re making sure of that in more ways than one. With adidas and the new #adizero SL I'm committing to a new PB.

The #adizero SL was created with high-speed in mind, and the Lightstrike Pro foam in the forefoot is designed to maintain performance.

Have another level of excitement to hop in the best with the best behind me. No better way to share the time I'm committed to beating than putting it on the newly added piece to the arsenal that’s gonna make it happen. 

#adizero SL #createdwithadidas

The World's greatest track and field stars are coming to Running City USA! 

Excited to see today’s announcement that the inaugural adidas Atlanta City Games will be held in Centennial Olympic Park on May 6. 

From sprints, to hurdles, to a road mile and pole vault, this is going to be a great way to showcase the sport in an iconic location. More details on how to watch and what athletes are competing, coming soon!

#RunningCityUSA #adidasAtlantaCityGames

He’s ready to put Team USA on his back 🇺🇸
 
Defending U.S. champ @BryceHoppel looks smooth en route to victory in the men’s 800m at the NYC Grand Prix in a SB of 1:44.55.
 
In his post-race interview, Hoppel made it clear he wants to end the American medal drought in the event.
 
📸: @jzsnapz

Defending the title

📸: @jzsnapz

social_posts.post_text:
Turning the track into a cage match! 😱
 
In one of the most physical 800m races you’ll ever see, experience wins out as @BryceHoppel defends his U.S. title in 1:46.20.
 
Veteran racers Isaiah Harris and Clayton Murphy crossed the line 2nd and 3rd and, pending any appeals, will head to Budapest with him.
 
📸: @justinbritton
